A GLASGOW student has won Trail magazine's UK Mountain Photo of the Year award with an image he took on a supermarket camera bought for £10. £10 camera photo wins £2k prize A GLASGOW student has won Trail magazine's UK Mountain Photo of the Year award with an image he took on a supermarket camera bought for £10.Ross Campbell, 27, entered a picture of a winter wild camp at the foot of Ben Lui mountain - and was the runaway winner, scooping 23% of the overall vote.Ross's prize is &pound;2000 of Nikon photography gear. 